      "side": 1,
      "message": "setRecursiveLock is basically just detecting whether the call to rdlock will come from the same thread that already has it, and makes it a no-op otherwise. The implementation of the recursive locking is to not actually recursively lock to avoid UB with recursive locks. I guess the wording of the title can be changed to \"disallow\" recursive locks to be more clear, but from the POV of the interface, it\u0027s \"allow\"ing them",
      "parentUuid": "835c7065_ce715ffc",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 147,
